    {
        "content": "<p>I learned it from André Joyal. I find the polynomial-functor interpretation even nicer than the one in species, also for the reasons Matteo expressed. And it fits very well with the dynamical viewpoint promoted by David. Differentiation of species is also due to Joyal, or course – it's in the original species paper <em>Une théorie combinatoire des séries formelles</em> (1981).</p>",
